As I pack up my studio, it is a good time reflect on the progress I've made. A year ago the only tools I had were a good set of pliers, a drill, and a dremel. I've invested everything I have back in. Now I'm upgrading to a larger studio, and in a couple days I'm releasing a fabrication that I'm very proud of. If it weren't for the love I have for this journey, and the love others have shown me, none of this would be possible. HUGE thank you to my family, friends, fellow artists, and complete strangers for the kind words and support🙏 
and a special thank you to my lovely lady @liz_ard_breath for putting up with my workaholic tendencies, and supporting this dream❤

{[Universally Unfurling]} •Hand-Fabricated .925 Sterling Silver
•50 x Multicolored Sapphire /Available/

Featuring a body of solid .925 sterling silver and a total of 50 multicolored sapphires (thanks to @candyman_crystals), this pendant is truly one of a kind. The silver unfurls from itself in an infinitely reproducing loop at the heart of this pendant. Extending out from the center is a series of symmetrical geometry and filigree carefully hand carved and replicating the growth of an unfurling fern. Sapphires coat the interior of this pendant bringing it to life as flashes of light dance across its surface in the sunlight. With a balanced orchestration of pink, orange, yellow, and purple sapphires this pendant is eye catching. Live on my Etsy now or through DM. Link in my bio. Much love ♥️♥️♥️
